{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_anw9qdz9n7mp0ybgapesd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"508590400","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/work/baseline-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nThis document describes the cache API implementation.\n\n## createCache()\n\nThe `createCache()` function creates and returns a new cache instance with the following methods.\n\n```javascript\nexport function createCache() { }\n```\n\nReturns an object containing the methods described below.\n\n## Methods\n\n### get\n\nThe `get(key)` method retrieves a value from the cache by key.\n\n```javascript\nget(key) { return values.get(key) }\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `key` - The key to look up in the cache\n\n**Returns:** The cached value, or `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n### set\n\nThe `set(key, value)` method stores a value in the cache.\n\n```javascript\nset(key, value) { values.set(key, value); return value }\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `key` - The key to store the value under\n- `value` - The value to store\n\n**Returns:** The value that was set.\n\n### delete\n\nThe `delete(key)` method removes a value from the cache by key.\n\n```javascript\ndelete(key) { return values.delete(key) }\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `key` - The key to delete from the cache\n\n**Returns:** `true` if the key existed and was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n\n### clear\n\nThe `clear()` method removes all entries from the cache.\n\n```javascript\nclear() { values.clear() }\n```\n\n**Returns:** `void`\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4665,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4557},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f322eb50-c377-4d3b-ae05-f0e35a3bad7d","uuid":"106f6d22-c8a0-4867-91fa-f264a7c180a2","timestamp":"2026-07-23T01:45:17.782Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"508590400","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /work/baseline-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f322eb50-c377-4d3b-ae05-f0e35a3bad7d","uuid":"e5d667bc-9d4d-45e8-92d5-7efa593b042a","timestamp":"2026-07-23T01:45:17.791Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/work/baseline-docs-from-code-2/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nThis document describes the cache API implementation.\n\n## createCache()\n\nThe `createCache()` function creates and returns a new cache instance with the following methods.\n\n```javascript\nexport function createCache() { }\n```\n\nReturns an object containing the methods described below.\n\n## Methods\n\n### get\n\nThe `get(key)` method retrieves a value from the cache by key.\n\n```javascript\nget(key) { return values.get(key) }\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `key` - The key to look up in the cache\n\n**Returns:** The cached value, or `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n### set\n\nThe `set(key, value)` method stores a value in the cache.\n\n```javascript\nset(key, value) { values.set(key, value); return value }\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `key` - The key to store the value under\n- `value` - The value to store\n\n**Returns:** The value that was set.\n\n### delete\n\nThe `delete(key)` method removes a value from the cache by key.\n\n```javascript\ndelete(key) { return values.delete(key) }\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `key` - The key to delete from the cache\n\n**Returns:** `true` if the key existed and was deleted, `false` otherwise.\n\n### clear\n\nThe `clear()` method removes all entries from the cache.\n\n```javascript\nclear() { values.clear() }\n```\n\n**Returns:** `void`\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
